%e A390762 a(7) = 1 since 7 = (1-1)^2 + (3-1)^2 + (3-1)^2/2 + (3-1)^2/4 with 3 prime.
%e A390762 a(120) = 1 since 120 = (5-1)^2 + (11-1)^2 + (1-1)^2/2 + (5-1)^2/4 with 5 and 11 prime.
%e A390762 a(754) = 1 since 754 = (17-1)^2 + (17-1)^2 + (23-1)^2/2 + (1-1)^2/4 with 17 and 23 both prime.
%e A390762 a(770) = 1 since 770 = (1-1)^2 + (17-1)^2 + (31-1)^2/2 + (17-1)^2/4 with 17 and 31 both prime.
%e A390762 a(1186) = 1 since 1186 = (1-1)^2 + (29-1)^2 + (3-1)^2/2 + (41-1)^2/4 with 29, 3 and 41 prime.
%e A390762 a(2290) = 1 since 2290 = (13-1)^2 + (37-1)^2 + (31-1)^2/2 + (41-1)^2/4 with 13, 37, 31 and 41 all prime.
